c:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 09 Nov 2023 18:25:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699553748</ingested><modified> 2023-11-09T18:15:58+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hobbies & Personal Activities]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1500" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/8e7e0660-7f27-11ee-afff-2e61ac2d331d" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1500" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/8e7e0660-7f27-11ee-afff-2e61ac2d331d" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Native Instruments]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Product photo of the Native Instruments Maschine MK3 all-in-one production studio. The primarily black device has colorful drum pads, and various knobs and buttons on its complex but modern / attractive face.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Native Instruments Maschine MK3]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Humane's Ai Pin costs $699 and ships in early 2024, which is about all we know for certain]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>可穿戴初创公司 Humane AI 几个月来一直在透露其即将推出的设备 AI Pin 的详细信息。我们第一次<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gMsQO5u7-NQ">在 5 月份的 TED 演讲</a>中看到它，最近在周四正式揭晓之前的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/humane-shows-off-its-futuristic-ai-pin-wearable-113510130.html">巴黎时装周</a>上一睹其承诺的功能。然而，关于可穿戴人工智能如何真正做到其所说的许多问题仍有待解答。</p><p>我们所知道的是：Humane 是一家由前苹果员工创立的备受瞩目的初创公司。它的第一个产品是 Humane AI Pin，这是一种口袋式可穿戴人工智能助手，据报道可以执行许多现代手机和数字助理所做的任务，但外形却截然不同。它没有屏幕，据报道主要通过语音命令进行操作，偶尔通过投影到用户手上的虚拟屏幕进行操作。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/humanes-ai-pin-will-reportedly-cost-699-235018028.html">它的价格为 700 美元</a>，另加 24 美元，因为 Humane 坚持在 T-Mobile 网络之上推出自己的 MVNO（移动虚拟网络运营商）。每月 24 美元的“人道订阅”包括 Pin 的专用手机号码，可以无限通话、文本和数据，而不是让设备与您现有的手机绑定。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/9106ad10-7f27-11ee-bff3-2bb26d3cbd37" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/9106ad10-7f27-11ee-bff3-2bb26d3cbd37" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="人性化的AI Pin" data-uuid="f249e673-5246-3011-a138-fba7cdca5c79"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">人性化的人工智能</div></figure><p>当订单于 2024 年初开始发货时，该设备本身将提供 Eclipse、Equinox 和 Lunar 三种颜色。将设备固定在衣服上的磁性夹子兼作电池存储功能，并包含一对备用电池，供用户使用和他们在一起。根据该公司的新闻稿，AI Pin 还配备超宽 RGB 摄像头、深度和运动传感器，所有这些都可以让“设备看到你所看到的世界”。</p><p>据报道，AI Pin 将在 Snapdragon 处理器上运行，并配有专用的 Qualcomm AI 引擎，支持其定制的 Cosmos 操作系统。据报道，其“全新的人工智能软件框架，Ai Bus”消除了将内容实际下载到设备本身的需要。相反，它“快速了解您的需求，立即将您连接到正确的人工智能体验或服务。”据报道，与微软和 OpenAI 的合作将使 AI Pin “能够访问一些世界上最强大的人工智能模型和平台。”</p><p>然而，关于 AI Pin，我们还有很多不了解的地方，比如每个电池模块的续航时间以及系统的防篡改系统锁定“受损”设备的敏感程度。迄今为止，该技术的现场演示很少见，实践机会几乎不存在。 Humane 将于周四下午举办首次活动，届时将展示 AI Pin 的功能迭代。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/ humanes-ai-pin-costs-699-and-ships-in-early-2024-which-is-about-all-we-know-for -certain-181048809.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/humanes-ai-pin-costs-699-and-ships-in-early-2024-which-is-about-all-we-know-for-certain-181048809.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5e535e27-e61c-4191-9190-a5987f7b5b10</guid><dc:creator>安德鲁·塔兰托拉</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 09 Nov 2023 18:10:48 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699564331</ingested><modified> 2023-11-09T21:12:15+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Andrew Tarantola]]></category><media:content height="2160" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/090b88e0-7f31-11ee-bfd3-71aa8ea6689a" width="3840"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2160" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/090b88e0-7f31-11ee-bfd3-71aa8ea6689a" width="3840"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Humane ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A cropped image showing the torso of a women wearing a camouflage jacket with a yellow Humane AI Pin on the chest.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Humane AI Pin]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Steam Deck OLED review: It's just better]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>关于<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://store.steampowered.com/steamdeck/">Steam Deck OLED，</a>首先要了解的是，它<em>不是</em>Steam Deck 2。Steam Deck OLED <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://ouryahoo.slack.com/archives/C04T1M9ENH2/p1699563681267939?thread_ts=1699561048.061759&amp;cid=C04T1M9ENH2">是 Valve 的中期更新</a>，类似于 Switch OLED 升级，但内部还有更多内容。它的屏幕更好，电池寿命更好，拇指杆更好，触觉更好，芯片和散热更好。没有改变的一件事是它的外形——它仍然是手持设备上最大的婴儿之一。 </p><div id="6abcb98210164bbf8392c69a7e3ad126"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dVRzZL1RQIc?si=yYdJwinHr0OaDayE" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p>新的 Steam Deck 的主要升级是它的 OLED 屏幕，它取代了原来的 LCD，最重要的是，它原生支持 HDR 和更快的帧速率。 OLED 还具有更小的边框，使得显示屏比原来的 7 英寸屏幕更大，达到 7.4 英寸。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="efaafd81bd134340baee8481de2d6954" data-type="product-list"></p><h2> OLED屏幕</h2><p>HDR OLED 显示屏看起来棒极了。它具有更宽的 P3 色域、纯黑色和 1,000 尼特的峰值亮度，而原始最高亮度为 400 尼特。实际上，这意味着屏幕的边框与任何游戏的黑色融为一体，为复古的宽高比创造出更加精致的框架，并为更高对比度的颜色提供空间。新型号的屏幕不支持可变刷新率 (VRR)，但现在最高可达 90Hz，而原来的屏幕只能达到 60Hz。更新后的显示屏光滑、清晰、明亮，就像一个完美的柠檬馅饼。 （即便如此，我也不建议舔屏幕。）</p><h2>电池寿命</h2><p>第一个 Steam Deck 的缺点之一是电池寿命短，最长只能达到 8 小时，而且只有在理想条件下才有效。 Valve 表示，新的 Steam Deck 电池续航时间将延长 30% 至 50%，具体取决于您的游戏方式，而且充电速度更快——该公司声称，45 分钟内即可从 20% 充至 80%。</p><h2>定制 AMD APU</h2><p> Steam Deck OLED 具有原始 Steam Deck 中定制 AMD APU 的模具缩小版 - 相同的 CPU 和 GPU，只是效率更高。这是索尼用来构建 PS4 Slim 和 PS5 Slim 的过程，但 Valve 没有将 Steam Deck 折叠在较小的硬件周围，而是选择在其现有底盘上添加更大的电池和更大的风扇。对于开发者来说，这意味着该设备具有与原始设备相同的性能目标，并且无需专门为新硬件创建游戏。最终，该设备的重量比原来的型号轻了约 30 克，相当于四分之五。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e071a270-7f0d-11ee-8abf-5681903f09a1" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e071a270-7f0d-11ee-8abf-5681903f09a1" style="height:1350px;width:2400px;" alt="蒸汽甲板 OLED" data-uuid="9632675a-5a9a-3a5a-b3bb-2e4c70188ccb"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">恩杰特</div></figure><h2>正在使用</h2><p>这给我们带来了一个关于我的小帮派的坏消息。 Steam Deck OLED 的尺寸与原版相同：11.7 英寸长、4.5 英寸高、近 2 英寸厚。新型号上的操纵杆实际上比第一个版本高 1 毫米。这是我<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/steam-deck-review-small-hands-180026719.html">第一次评测 Steam Deck 时</a>对它的主要抱怨之一：我的手比一般人小，而且当我握住 Steam Deck 时，它的外观和感觉都非常可笑。无论我修指甲多久，它都太大了。不过，OLED 型号给人的感觉比原来的更加平衡。它不那么头重脚轻，而且从技术上来说它的重量也更轻。这些微小的调整在我的游戏过程中产生了明显的变化，而且该设备作为手持设备感觉更易于管理——或者也许我只是被它所有明亮、漂亮的颜色分散了注意力，而没有关心我手掌的抽筋。</p><p>新手持设备上的拇指操纵杆具有改进的纹理，使用几个月后不会变灰，而且到目前为止感觉非常好用。 In my hands-on time so far, I&#39;ve found that the OLED touchscreen responds immediately to input, and the haptic feedback on the built-in trackpads feels even more precise, populating in reactive pin-pricks under the textured plastic.</p><p> I spent a few cozy nights on my couch swapping between the LCD and OLED Steam Decks, and honestly, after I&#39;m done with this review, I&#39;ll probably retire my original model. The Steam Deck OLED is sharper and more responsive; indie games, AAA games and plain old Steam menus look so much better on the new hardware. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e07ffa50-7f0d-11ee-bdde-3efa5c81fa1b" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e07ffa50-7f0d-11ee-bdde-3efa5c81fa1b" style="height:1350px;width:2400px;" alt="蒸汽甲板 OLED" data-uuid="048d6cb1-8eae-33ab-90c8-98ebbfe80968"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">恩杰特</div></figure><p><em>Hades</em> is my most-played game on the original Steam Deck, so I used that to test out Valve&#39;s battery life claims. Though it doesn&#39;t support HDR, a game like <em>Hades</em> pops on the OLED, and its animations look more fluid than on the LCD version. The OLED lasted four hours and 23 minutes before dying. With the same settings (800p with a 60 fps cap and similar brightness) the original model died after two hours and 42 minutes. That&#39;s a 62 percent improvement, surpassing Valve&#39;s own estimates, though batteries degrade and I&#39;ve had my LCD Steam Deck since the device&#39;s launch in early 2022. In a stress test that involved playing <em>Elden Ring</em> with everything maxed out, the OLED battery lasted two hours and 20 minutes, about 40 percent longer than the original.</p><p> Playing the Steam Decks back-to-back highlighted another significant quality-of-life improvement: heat management. My palms have gotten toasty playing the OLED model, but they haven&#39;t broken a sweat like they often do with the original. The new fan may be larger, but it&#39;s not any louder, and it clearly works a treat.</p><p> The Steam Deck OLED has a new Wi-Fi 6E module and improved antennas that should enable faster downloads for anyone with a compatible router. I don&#39;t have a 6E router or multi-gigabit Wi-Fi, but with a regular Wi-Fi 6 router, the top download speed I saw on the new Steam Deck was 562mbps, which was about 10 percent faster than the old Steam Deck, and 10 percent slower than the speeds I get on my MacBook Pro. The device uses Bluetooth 5.3 and adds a dedicated antenna, which should improve functionality when using Wi-Fi and Bluetooth at the same time. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e08acfc0-7f0d-11ee-b7ff-803c9ea24782" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e08acfc0-7f0d-11ee-b7ff-803c9ea24782" style="height:1350px;width:2400px;" alt="蒸汽甲板 OLED" data-uuid="cd5b07c3-a095-3f40-854f-0f27c30903c0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">恩杰特</div></figure><p>Even with improvements to the battery, thermals and weight distribution, the Steam Deck OLED is still more of a Wii U than a Vita. It&#39;s a beast of a handheld, and it makes the most sense as a portable console to use around the house, rather than a truly travel-ready device. The new model even comes with an extra-long, 2.5m charging cable, designed specifically with couch-based players in mind. I didn&#39;t test out the docking station with the new Steam Deck, but Valve recently released <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/1675200/view/3686804163591367815">a SteamOS update</a> that lets players take advantage of HDR and VRR on external displays, which only drives home the Wii U-ness of it all.</p><p> As far as software, you know the drill by now. Valve has rolled out labels for Steam games signifying how well they&#39;ll work on the handheld, with four levels: unknown, unsupported, playable and verified. Playable games generally come with a small caveat, like having to deploy the on-screen keyboard, while verified games have been fully optimized for portable play. Currently, more than 10,000 titles on Steam fall under the playable or verified labels, with more added every day.</p><h2> When will the Steam Deck OLED be available?</h2><p> The Steam Deck OLED will go on sale on November 16th at 1pm ET, and Valve has units ready to ship that same day. The company has lowered the price of its LCD lineup and will sell through its backstock of 64GB and 512GB models until they&#39;re all gone. It&#39;ll continue selling the 256GB LCD model at a reduced price of $400, while the 512GB OLED model will cost $550 and the 1TB OLED model will cost $650. There&#39;s also a limited edition 1TB OLED version priced at $680 that comes with a special carrying case, a translucent gray body and orange accents. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/59e2a780-7f0e-11ee-bcdb-82f3bbec050f" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/59e2a780-7f0e-11ee-bcdb-82f3bbec050f" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="Steam Deck OLED limited edition" data-uuid="bd5139a8-a8ea-3c19-892d-24d07c4e7494"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">阀门</div></figure><h2>包起来</h2><p>According to the developers I spoke with at Valve, this is the definitive version of the Steam Deck. The HDR OLED model is what they would have released the first time around, if the technology had existed before 2022. The handheld market has evolved quickly — in just over a year, the Steam Deck <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/handheld-gaming-pc-retro-indie-handhelds-steam-deck-playdate-150038001.html">proved there&#39;s widespread demand</a> for handheld PCs, and its success helped drive chip makers and display manufacturers to build hardware specifically for high-fidelity mobile play. This is great news for Valve and the Steam Deck, and also the <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-handheld-gaming-system-140018863.html">other handhelds</a> coming out of companies like Ayaneo, ASUS, Ayn, Logitech, Retroid and Razer. Hell, maybe even <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/playdate-review-indie-games-crank-170054294.html">Playdate</a> will get an HDR OLED display one day. (Just kidding; Playdate is literally perfect).</p><p> So, no, the HDR OLED refresh isn&#39;t the Steam Deck 2, but it is a welcome improvement on an already good device. The <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://store.steampowered.com/steamdeck/">Steam Deck OLED</a> is the facetuned, photoshopped, spit-shined version of Valve&#39;s handheld, and it features tangible, clever improvements. The updated display is the highlight of the device, while things like faster charging, improved antennas and smoother haptics are welcome bonuses. More importantly, this is Valve renewing its commitment to portable PC gaming, and that&#39;s a relief to see. The Steam Deck is the granddaddy of handheld PCs and Valve has the resources to continue innovating in this space. For now, the OLED model is a half-step toward the Steam Deck 2, which may be the final version of the device — unless Valve finally learns how to count to three.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/steam-deck-oled-review-its-just-better-180038030.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/steam-deck-oled-review-its-just-better-180038030.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7e4188af-b6a0-4ada-9a54-9f123d982166</guid><dc:creator> Jessica Conditt</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 09 Nov 2023 18:00:38 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699564663</ingested><modified> 2023-11-09T21:17:49+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="1350" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e06dd1e0-7f0d-11ee-977a-91b5834194b4" width="2400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1350" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/e06dd1e0-7f0d-11ee-977a-91b5834194b4" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Steam Deck OLED]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Steam Deck OLED]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Steam Deck OLED arrives November 16 with an improved screen and longer battery life]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>惊喜！ Valve has announced a new Steam Deck and — double surprise — we&#39;ve <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/steam-deck-oled-review-its-just-better-180038030.html">already reviewed it</a> . It might not look like a big change from the outside, but the Steam Deck OLED is a thorough mid-cycle refresh of a machine that&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/steam-deck-review-small-hands-180026719.html">not even two years old</a> . At the same time, Valve is also adjusting the configuration of its entry-level model, making it a far more compelling option. Apologies to anyone who literally bought a Steam Deck yesterday.</p><p> At an event held for press prior to the device&#39;s launch, Greg Coomer, a product designer at Valve, called the new model &quot;the definitive version of the Steam Deck.&quot; He explained that the device contains many things the company wanted to include at the LCD model&#39;s launch but wasn&#39;t able to, along with some additions based on community feedback. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="52cb98be6fe64f15b47de8353cfec21f"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_vTsZMvjJ-A?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div><p> As its name suggests, the most noticeable upgrade to the Steam Deck OLED is the display. The original Steam Deck had a 7-inch 800p LCD running at 60Hz. The new model squeezes a 7.4-inch OLED screen into the same space, significantly shrinking the bezels around the display. The new panel runs at the same resolution, but with a refresh rate of up to 90Hz. It&#39;s also HDR, covering 110 percent of the P3 color space with a peak brightness of 1,000 nits — the old model maxed out at around 400 nits. Like all OLED screens, it has pure blacks and near-instantaneous response times. As before, anti-glare etched glass is available, but only on the premium model.</p><p> The Steam Deck OLED has a die-shrunk version of the same custom APU found in the original Steam Deck. The new APU is produced on a 6nm process, rather than the older 7nm process. Manufacturers typically use die-shrinks to either improve performance or efficiency, and Valve has chosen the latter. The max frequency of both the GPU and CPU are identical between the LCD and OLED models, so for developers tuning their games for Steam Decks, they only have a single performance target.</p><p> In concert with the more-efficient processor, there&#39;s also a 25 percent larger battery with a 50Whr capacity, compared to the original&#39;s 40Whr. According to Valve, these changes combined result in a 30-50 percent increase in longevity between the two generations — the official battery life claim is &quot;three to 12 hours.&quot; In our review, we measured a playtime increase of 62 percent when playing <em>Hades</em> on the OLED model versus our 18-month-old original. (Batteries degrade over time, which explains why our gains were more pronounced.)</p><p> The new internals make the Steam Deck OLED marginally lighter, and also cooler to the touch when playing games, aided by a slightly larger fan. Other improvements include support for both Wi-Fi 6E and Bluetooth 5.3, together with a new antenna array that will give a better experience when using both at the same time. There&#39;s also a reworked power supply (it has a logo now!) with a longer 2.5m cable that will charge the OLED model from 20 to 80 percent in “as little as 45 minutes.” The thumbsticks have also been made 1mm taller, and the touch pads&#39; haptics are slightly sharper. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/2dba5640-7f03-11ee-bfbd-794e4e0553fb" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/2dba5640-7f03-11ee-bfbd-794e4e0553fb" style="height:1350px;width:2400px;" alt="Steam Deck OLED lifestyle image" data-uuid="725e8c05-5f66-3f05-a50f-d5fd534023d4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">阀门</div></figure><p>The Steam Deck OLED starts at $549, and will replace all but the entry-level model in the range. The immediate reality is a bit of a mess and a little complicated, but this, Valve says, will be the Steam Deck line-up moving forward:</p><ul><li><p> 256GB Steam Deck LCD ($399)</p></li><li><p> 512GB Steam Deck OLED ($549)</p></li><li><p> 1TB Steam Deck OLED ($649)</p></li></ul><p> As a result of the changes, the 64GB LCD Steam Deck (previously sold at $399) will drop to $349, and the 512GB LCD (previously $649) will drop to $499. Once Valve sells through its inventory of both, those lines will be discontinued. Valve says it will continue to support all LCD models with software updates.</p><p> So, the long-term lineup starts at the same $399 price, which gets you the old LCD Steam Deck, but with 256GB of storage instead of 64GB. The new step-up model costs $20 more at $549, but comes with an OLED display and the improvements outlined above, plus double the storage. The range still tops out at $649, but you&#39;re getting a lot more for your money: All of the hardware improvements, 1TB of storage instead of 512GB and an improved carry case that can pop out into a slimmer shell that&#39;s smaller and easier to fit in a bag. As mentioned, it also has the same anti-glare etched glass as the outgoing 512GB LCD model.</p><p> Finally, there&#39;s also a Limited Edition version of the 1TB model, with a translucent shell and a customized carry case, which will be sold at $679. We imagine stocks will not last very long, as it looks pretty rad: </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/dbdbc7a0-7f02-11ee-bff7-acf08dc0f7b4" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/dbdbc7a0-7f02-11ee-bff7-acf08dc0f7b4" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="Steam Deck OLED Limited Edition" data-uuid="83d2e074-6f14-38c1-9125-749dfbbec612"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">阀门</div></figure><p>While there are no concrete updates on future hardware developments, Valve engineer Pierre-Loup Griffais noted that, so long as interest in handheld gaming remains high, the company has &quot;plans for successive generations of handhelds.&quot; For now, Griffais explained, it&#39;s important to Valve that developers don&#39;t need to &quot;split their attention&quot; between different performance targets.</p><p> When asked about the potential for future hardware — like a return of the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2015-10-15-alienware-steam-machine-review.html">Steam Machine</a> or an updated Steam Controller — there were no firm updates, but there does seem to be <em>something</em> happening. Griffais agreed that enabling the Steam Deck to work as a hybrid living room console was a &quot;side goal&quot; of the team, and noted that everything Valve does to improve SteamOS will benefit other devices. Coomer added that Valve is still working internally on &quot;a bunch of controllers and prototypes.&quot; If SteamOS is being used on larger displays, the team would want to augment that experience with better input options. &quot;We don&#39;t have any announcements on that front, but it&#39;s why we&#39;re building prototypes and thinking about the future there,&quot; Coomer said.</p><p> The Steam Deck OLED will be available to order on November 16th at 1PM ET. Valve expects units to begin shipping as soon as orders start to roll in. The updated pricing on the existing LCD models is <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://store.steampowered.com/steamdeck/">already in effect</a> .</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-steam-deck-oled-arrives-november-16-with-an-improved-screen-and-longer-battery-life-180032945.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-steam-deck-oled-arrives-november-16-with-an-improved-screen-and-longer-battery-life-180032945.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> afd1a171-b529-41d6-b69f-88e3b5e8f7f6</guid><dc:creator> Jessica Conditt,Aaron Souppouris</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 09 Nov 2023 18:00:32 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699563644</ingested><modified> 2023-11-09T21:00:51+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="1350" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/58fa60d0-7f02-11ee-8759-56bff6b88746" width="2400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1350" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/58fa60d0-7f02-11ee-8759-56bff6b88746" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Valve]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Steam Deck OLED]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Steam Deck OLED]]></media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>